arch:property.oc:show_val: X6 is a human ilium. LY 2001: The bone from this unit largely consists of long bone shaft and rib fragments of both 03 and 07 size animals. Very few are identifiable to species level. Evidence of burning is infrequent but where present the bone has been carbonised. Digested bone is present in low proportions. Amongst the identifiable portion was a distal cattle tibia that contained plaster on the articular surface, the shaft survives to 10 cm and forms a point in the centre but it is not possible to ascertain if this was deliberate, accidental or a feature of postdepositional damage. A massive distal cattle radius also displayed some of this same plaster on its distal end. X7 is a piece of antler probably of fallow deer given the presence of flat portions on the piece. A couple of pieces of fish bone were recovered from the dry sieve. 4mm sample #1 was recorded for diagnostics only. Last number = 92.

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
